<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFF62FE70FEC0FDD7" bold="true" box="[199,334,506,532]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the 
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFB4C91BFD10FE70FD6BFDD7" box="[693,741,506,532]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality; noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFB4C91BFF62FD97FE48FD67" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB4C91BFF62FD97FE48FD67" blockId="21.[151,1437,325,676]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFF62FD97FECCFDF4" bold="true" box="[199,322,541,567]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB4C91BFE69FD94FDDDFDFB" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[460,595,542,568]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tabatinga" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFE69FD94FDDDFDFB" box="[460,595,542,568]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. tabatinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFDFEFD94FD40FDFB" bold="true" box="[603,718,542,568]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFB4C91BFDFEFD94FD40FDFB" box="[603,718,542,568]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB4C91BFC07FD94FBB7FDFB" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1880" box="[930,1081,542,568]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keyserlingi">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFC07FD94FBB7FDFB" box="[930,1081,542,568]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. keyserlingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB4C91BFBEDFD94FB47FDFB" box="[1096,1225,542,568]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1793,1817]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,195,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[154,1434,181,1769]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Sadala keyserlingi Simon 24–26 Male (INPA 4563), left palp (24 prolateral, 25 ventral, 26 retrolateral); 27–29 Female (MNHN 2459, syntype) (27 epigyne, 28 vulva, 29 schematic course of internal duct system). C—conductor; DpP—dorsal proximal projection; E—embolus; FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; TP—triangular projection; PTA—prolateral tibial projection; RTA—retrolateral tibial apophysis; SP—spermathecae; st—second turn of duct system; ST—subtegulum. Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550215/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figs 27–29</figureCitation>
) by the vulva with FW dilated, at least three times wider from CO to first turn than between first and second turns (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB4C91BFB74FDC8FAABFD9E" box="[1233,1317,578,605]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–67" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,752,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-286@20.[168,1420,741,1778]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 62–67. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 62–64 (ex MNHN 2459) (62 epigyne, 63 vulva, 64 schematic course of internal duct system); 65–67 (AMNH, paratype) (65 epigyne, 66 vulva, 67 schematic course of internal duct system). Scale lines: 1 mm. FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; st—second turn of duct system; TP—triangular projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550239/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
). They are distinguished from the latter species by the epigyne with slightly pear-shaped MS (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB4C91BFB96FDECFB06FD42" box="[1075,1160,614,641]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–67" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,752,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-286@20.[168,1420,741,1778]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 62–67. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 62–64 (ex MNHN 2459) (62 epigyne, 63 vulva, 64 schematic course of internal duct system); 65–67 (AMNH, paratype) (65 epigyne, 66 vulva, 67 schematic course of internal duct system). Scale lines: 1 mm. FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; st—second turn of duct system; TP—triangular projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550239/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Figs 62</figureCitation>
) (triangular in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB4C91BFA95FDECFF44FD67" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1880" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keyserlingi">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFA95FDECFF44FD67" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">S. keyserlingi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF416671FFB4C91BFF32F820FC80F825" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550243" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6550243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550243/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" startId="21.[151,264,1962,1986]" targetBox="[180,1405,702,1924]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB4C91BFF32F820FC80F825" blockId="21.[151,1436,1962,2023]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFF32F820FED6F801" bold="true" box="[151,344,1962,1986]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">FIGURES 68–71.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFFB4C91BFEC4F820FD9CF801" authority="Rheims &amp; Jäger, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" box="[353,530,1962,1986]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Sadala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tabatinga" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFEC4F820FD9CF801" box="[353,530,1962,1986]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sadala tabatinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB4C91BFDB9F821FD09F800" bold="true" box="[540,647,1963,1987]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FFB4C91BFDB9F821FD09F800" box="[540,647,1963,1987]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female 68–69 (CHNUFPI 2454, holotype) (68 epigyne, 69 vulva); 70–71 (AMNH, paratype) (70 epigyne, 71 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFB7C918FF62FF1CFB1EFDDA" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB7C918FF62FF1CFC85FE49" blockId="22.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB7C918FF62FF1CFDCDFF73" bold="true" box="[199,579,150,177]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Description, Female (
<typeStatus id="5485885BFFB7C918FE6DFF1CFDB8FF73" box="[456,566,150,176]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">holotype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length 15.3. Prosoma: 6.6 long, 6.2 wide. Opisthosoma: 8.5 long, 4.7 wide. Eyes: diameters: 0.55, 0.40, 0.35, 0.40; interdistances: 0.35, 0.30, 0.65, 0.72, 0.40, 0.35. Legs: I: absent; II: 31.1 (9.0, 3.5, 8.1, 8.2, 2.3); III: 22.2 (6.7, 2.7, 5.7, 5.5, 1.6); IV: 23.9 (7.5, 2.7, 6.3, 5.6, 1.8). Spination follows the generic pattern except patellae I–IV: d0. Epigyne: EF slightly wider than long; MAB embedded in EF; MS almost two times longer than wide, widest medially, slightly constricted anteriorly; TP slightly wider than long; LL touching posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FE2CFEC1FE6EFEA6" box="[393,480,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–67" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,752,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-286@20.[168,1420,741,1778]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 62–67. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 62–64 (ex MNHN 2459) (62 epigyne, 63 vulva, 64 schematic course of internal duct system); 65–67 (AMNH, paratype) (65 epigyne, 66 vulva, 67 schematic course of internal duct system). Scale lines: 1 mm. FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; st—second turn of duct system; TP—triangular projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550239/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 62</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FE49FEC1FD82FEA5" box="[492,524,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–71" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[180,1405,702,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-181@21.[165,1422,700,1939]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 68–71. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 68–69 (CHNUFPI 2454, holotype) (68 epigyne, 69 vulva); 70–71 (AMNH, paratype) (70 epigyne, 71 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550243/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">68</figureCitation>
). Vulva: FW posteriad; GP as wide as long, arising from ducts at second turn; SP irregularly rounded; FD antero laterad (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FDF7FEE5FD5DFE4A" box="[594,723,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–67" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,752,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-286@20.[168,1420,741,1778]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 62–67. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 62–64 (ex MNHN 2459) (62 epigyne, 63 vulva, 64 schematic course of internal duct system); 65–67 (AMNH, paratype) (65 epigyne, 66 vulva, 67 schematic course of internal duct system). Scale lines: 1 mm. FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; st—second turn of duct system; TP—triangular projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550239/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 63–64</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FD7BFEE5FD70FE49" box="[734,766,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–71" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[180,1405,702,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-181@21.[165,1422,700,1939]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 68–71. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 68–69 (CHNUFPI 2454, holotype) (68 epigyne, 69 vulva); 70–71 (AMNH, paratype) (70 epigyne, 71 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550243/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">69</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB7C918FF62FE19FE04FE6E" blockId="22.[151,1437,150,573]" box="[199,394,403,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB7C918FF62FE19FE83FE6E" bold="true" box="[199,269,403,429]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Male:</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB7C918FF62FE3CFB1EFDDA" blockId="22.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB7C918FF62FE3CFEB1FE13" bold="true" box="[199,319,438,464]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Variation.</emphasis>
Females (n = 4): total length 15.3–18.5; prosoma length 6.6–7.5; femur I length 8.3–8.9. Epigyne: MS slightly shorter, less than two times longer than wide; TP slightly anterior to posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FAACFE51FAECFE36" box="[1289,1378,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–67" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,752,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-286@20.[168,1420,741,1778]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 62–67. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 62–64 (ex MNHN 2459) (62 epigyne, 63 vulva, 64 schematic course of internal duct system); 65–67 (AMNH, paratype) (65 epigyne, 66 vulva, 67 schematic course of internal duct system). Scale lines: 1 mm. FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; st—second turn of duct system; TP—triangular projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550239/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 65</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FAD5FE51FA1EFE36" box="[1392,1424,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–71" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[180,1405,702,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-181@21.[165,1422,700,1939]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 68–71. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 68–69 (CHNUFPI 2454, holotype) (68 epigyne, 69 vulva); 70–71 (AMNH, paratype) (70 epigyne, 71 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550243/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">70</figureCitation>
). Vulva: internal ducts with FW more dilated covering second turn and GP (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FC72FE75FBD6FDDA" box="[983,1112,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 62–67" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1801,1825]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,752,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-286@20.[168,1420,741,1778]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 62–67. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 62–64 (ex MNHN 2459) (62 epigyne, 63 vulva, 64 schematic course of internal duct system); 65–67 (AMNH, paratype) (65 epigyne, 66 vulva, 67 schematic course of internal duct system). Scale lines: 1 mm. FD—fertilization duct; ft—first turn of duct system; GP—glandular projection; LL—lateral lobe; MS—median septum; st—second turn of duct system; TP—triangular projection." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550239" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550239/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 66–67</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FBC1FE75FB0DFDDA" box="[1124,1155,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–71" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[180,1405,702,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-181@21.[165,1422,700,1939]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 68–71. Sadala tabatinga spec. nov., female 68–69 (CHNUFPI 2454, holotype) (68 epigyne, 69 vulva); 70–71 (AMNH, paratype) (70 epigyne, 71 vulva). Scale lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550243/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">71</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3246572FFB7C918FF62FDA8FB4CFDFE" box="[199,1218,546,573]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8136F9FFB7C918FF62FDA8FB4CFDFE" blockId="22.[151,1437,150,573]" box="[199,1218,546,573]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFFB7C918FF62FDA8FEEFFDFF" bold="true" box="[199,353,546,572]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Distribution.</emphasis>
Northwestern South America, in 
<collectingCountry id="F3297669FFB7C918FD7CFDA9FCC9FDFE" box="[729,839,547,573]" name="Colombia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3297669FFB7C918FCDBFDA9FC4CFDFE" box="[894,962,547,573]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Amazonas) (
<figureCitation id="13052A7CFFB7C918FBC4FDA9FB38FDFE" box="[1121,1206,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 89–90" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1940,1964]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@27.[155,1432,181,1916]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 89–90. Distribution maps for Sadala spp. 89 S. tabatinga spec. nov., S. velox Simon, S. nanay spec. nov., S. punicea Simon 90 S. rufa (Keyserling), S. kaiabi spec. nov., S. keyserlingi Simon, S. nigristernis Simon, S. yuyapichis spec. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550257/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 89</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
